value.value: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of ratio of the bearer's output to the bearer's input.
A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's rate of change of momentum.

definition.value: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's length being notably higher than its width.
A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being narrow, with the two opposite margins parallel.

value.value: A quality which inheres in an process.
A quality which inheres in a continuant.
A color consisting of yellow hue and high brightness.

definition.value: A physical quality that inheres in an bearer by virtue of how that bearer interacts with electromagnetic radiation.

value.value: An EM radiation quality that is independent of the EM wavelength range.
A scalar EM radiation quality which obtains by the capacity of the bearer to scatter or reflect radiation.
A reflective quality restricted to a particular wavelength.
An EM radiation quality in which the EM radiation is within the fiat range of the spectrum visible deemed to be light.

definition.value: A temperature which is relatively high.
A temperature which is relatively low.

value.value: A process quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's magnitude of the temporal extent between the starting and ending point.
A 2-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's two dimensional extent.

definition.value: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lack of distinct morphology.

value.value: A length quality which is equal to the length of any straight line segment that passes through the center of a circle and whose endpoints are on the circular boundary.
A density quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of some influence exerted by the bearer's mass on a given area.
A density quality which is equal to the mass exerting an influence on a one-dimensional object.
A density quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of some influence exerted by the bearer's mass on a given volume.
A shape quality that obtains by virtue of the bearer having inward facing edges; having a surface or boundary that curves or bulges outward, as the exterior of a sphere.

definition.value: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having distinct structure.
A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking distinct structure.

value.value: A concentration quality inhering in a medium by virtue of the bearer's tendency to hydronate a specific reference base.
An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to produce new life or offspring.

definition.value: A sensitivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's dependence on oxygen.
A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's independence on oxygen.

value.value: A quality that is equal to the potential energy per unit charge associated with a static (time-invariant) electric field, also called the electrostatic potential.
A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's magnitude in respect to a related entity.

definition.value: A position which is relatively high.
A positional which is relatively low.
A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having an oblique or slanted direction.

value.value: A monadic quality of continuant inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being intricate and compounded.
A complexity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being intricate and compounded.

definition.value: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being turned, bowed, or twisted without breaking.
A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's inability of being turned, bowed, or twisted without breaking.

A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting the physical characteristics of an entity characterized by particles arranged such that their shape and volume are relatively stable.

value.value: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting the physical characteristics of an entity consisting of particles that have neither a defined volume nor defined shape.

definition.value: A physical quality inhering in an entity exhibiting the physical characteristics of an amorphous (non-crystalline) form of matter between a gas and a solid that has a definite volume, but no definite shape.

value.value: The number of parts of a particular type that the bearer entity has. This is a relational quality, and thus holds between two entities: the bearer of the quality, and the type of parts.

definition.value: A mass which is higher than normal or average.

value.value: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's motion characteristic.
A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to transmit of an entity through a medium.

definition.value: A surface shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a degree of bending.

value.value: A 1-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's downward or backward or inward dimension.

definition.value: A concentration quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's amount of osmoles of solute per liter of solution.
A osmolarity which is relatively high.

value.value: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's vertical distance of a point above or below a reference surface.

definition.value: An elevation which is relatively high.
